premise_source_doc_sentence: Monmouth Rebellion  (  1685  )  -- in England , The Monmouth Rebellion , also known as The Revolt of the West or The West Country rebellion , was an attempt to overthrow James II , who had become King of England , Scotland and Ireland upon the death of his elder brother Charles II on 6 February 1685 .
